    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Am so glad I found this interesting post. (Although a bit later than it was posted.)</p>
<p>Will definitely try it, as the ingredients are two of my favorites.</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-2627" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://outandup.wordpress.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">outandup</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/08/on-experimentation-and-an-unexpected-ice-cream-float/#comment-2627"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-20T03:47:42-04:00">Thursday, May 20, 2010 at 3:47 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I know this post is a million years old, but I am currently drinking a Rogue chocolate stout/Stonyfield After Dark Chocolate float. And, wow. It might be overkill. But it might also be my new favorite dessert.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-2628" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://myheadisagarden.wordpress.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Rose</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/08/on-experimentation-and-an-unexpected-ice-cream-float/#comment-2628"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-19T19:42:43-04:00">Monday, July 19, 2010 at 7:42 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Even though this post is ages old, I wanted to throw in my two cents. I love doing something very similar with Peche or Framboise Lambic and either a creamy french vanilla ice cream or a mango ice cream I found at Safeway. It&#39;s more summery with all that fruity goodness and the mango works well with both the peach or raspberry.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-2629" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Kamalei</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/08/on-experimentation-and-an-unexpected-ice-cream-float/#comment-2629"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-08-03T20:31:23-04:00">Tuesday, August 3, 2010 at 8:31 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I can so relate to being the cautious baker to my husbandʻs maverick chef. And my mother says the exact same thing about following a recipe exactly the first time! The Maui brewing company makes an excellent toasted coconut porter. I had a float with that and a scoop of tahititan vanilla bean ice cream at the Kona Brew Fest one year&#8211;divine!</p>
    </div>

